[SN]TITLE[SN]
The US school kids pedalling their way to success

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
One teacher in the US has found an unusual way to get her class to concentrate better - by installing bike pedals under the desks.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
11 October 2016 Last updated at 07:03 BST
The idea is that cycling during lessons helps the pupils to focus their energy and stop them from fidgeting.
Students at Martin GT Magnet Middle School in North Carolina tell Newsround what they think about it.
